      "text": "shortUrl\n- fast creation\n- unique\n- short (5-7 chars)",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "shortUrl\n- fast creation\n- unique\n- short (5-7 chars)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "zd0vh7zRbrMyOUNt-Zg85",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1779.2736463676583,
      "y": 1518.7485865465433,
      "width": 897.5987548828125,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1q",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1740952104,
      "version": 1568,
      "versionNonce": 127359064,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1751294617606,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. prefix of the long url\n\n2. random number generator, 10^9 >= 10 characters(0-9), need 12-13 chars\n    - base62 encoding : 0-9, A-Z, a-z\n    - 62^6 = 56B\n    - Collision prob : chances of 2 urls being same on choosing 1B random codes from 56B\n        Birthday paradox\n    - 880k collisions\n    - we just need to check for collisions first\n\n3. hash the long url\n    - hash func - sha256 etc, md5(longUrl) -> hash -> base62(hash)[:6]\n    - increases randomness if even one char is changed\n    - same as above\n\n4. Counter\n    - incrementing a counter -> base62 (start with 0, base62(0) for first user till 56Bth url\n    - its fast, of max 6 chars and unique as we are just linearly increasing\n    - predictability, security vulnerability, they know next shortUrl and can also scrape all longUrls\n        - \"warning, don't shorten private urls\"\n        - rate limiting\n    - bijective function (1-to-1 mapping)\n        - sqids.org, obfuscate the base62 shortUrl to something else\n\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. prefix of the long url\n\n2. random number generator, 10^9 >= 10 characters(0-9), need 12-13 chars\n    - base62 encoding : 0-9, A-Z, a-z\n    - 62^6 = 56B\n    - Collision prob : chances of 2 urls being same on choosing 1B random codes from 56B\n        Birthday paradox\n    - 880k collisions\n    - we just need to check for collisions first\n\n3. hash the long url\n    - hash func - sha256 etc, md5(longUrl) -> hash -> base62(hash)[:6]\n    - increases randomness if even one char is changed\n    - same as above\n\n4. Counter\n    - incrementing a counter -> base62 (start with 0, base62(0) for first user till 56Bth url\n    - its fast, of max 6 chars and unique as we are just linearly increasing\n    - predictability, security vulnerability, they know next shortUrl and can also scrape all longUrls\n        - \"warning, don't shorten private urls\"\n        - rate limiting\n    - bijective function (1-to-1 mapping)\n        - sqids.org, obfuscate the base62 shortUrl to something else\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
